president bush attended emperor hirohitos funeral 
friday taking a frontrow seat as the japanese waived protocol 
rules to give him a prominent position at the solemn shinjuku 
imperial garden ceremony 
in the hours preceding the funeral bushs attention was diverted 
by the continuing problems of defense secretarydesignate john 
tower the white house despite heavy overseas calling was unable 
to get the former texas senator approved by the senate armed 
services committee in washington it voted 119 to reject his 
nomination 
white house press secretary marlin fitzwater told reporters that 
bush was sticking by tower no matter how the committee vote went 
the next step is to consider it on the floor and thats what we 
will do he said 
a steady rain fell and the weather was chilly as bush and 
dignitaries from some 160 countries gathered for the funeral 
ceremony 
bush was shot down by japanese antiaircraft fire in world war 
ii but said coming to the funeral was the right thing to do and 
that he didnt want to look back 
wearing dark mourning clothes and a black overcoat with the 
collar raised bush was seated with his wife barbara on his right 
and west german president richard von weizsacker on his left 
the floor below them was heated with electrical coils and a 
brown wool blanket was placed on each chair 
en route to the funeral site bushs motorcade crossed an 
overpass just as the funeral procession containing hirohitos hearse 
