left the palace for the funeral motorcade 
a 21gun salute boomed from howitzers mingling with ancient 
court music played on pipes and drums crowds up to 10 deep watched 
the motorcade as it pulled out of the main gate of the palace moved 
across the moat and along its route 
the 13 hours of funeral ceremonies began with two hours of 
private shinto ceremonies presided over by the akihito 55 who 
ascended the chrysanthemum throne after his fathers death 
the body of hirohito who died of cancer jan 7 was encased in 
an inner wooden coffin and an outer one of metal 
before the procession officers joining the largest security 
operation in japanese history checked cars and patrolled streets 
absent from the public ceremonies was empress dowager nagako 
hirohitos 85yearold wife said to be ailing with back and hip 
problems the kyodo news agency said she paid her last respects 
during the palace ceremonies 
stores in the ginza shopping district covered their advertising 
