washington by the senate armed services committee the vote was 
119 split along party lines with the democrats in the majority 
the vote the first such committee rejection of a presidents 
cabinet choice in 44 years was a major setback for bush on his 
first trip overseas as president and came as he mingled with 
leaders of more than 160 countries 
i am going to strongly continue to back sen tower and i dont 
