<TEXT>
a lebanese shiite moslem was 
sentenced to life imprisonment today for the 1987 hijack of an air 
afrique jetliner in which he killed a french passenger and seriously 
wounded a flight attendant 
switzerlands highest court convicted hussein hariri on all seven 
charges against him including murder attempted murder and 
hostagetaking 
the 22yearold hariri who previously said a life sentence would 
be no problem rose from his chair but showed no emotion when 
the verdict was read he will be eligible for parole in 15 years 
the ruling by the fivemember federal criminal court followed a 
fourday trial in which the prosecution called hariri a killer 
blinded by conviction 
defense attorneys had sought a conviction on the lesser charge of 
manslaughter claiming hariri acted on reflex when he fatally shot 
xavier beaulieu 28 they said testimony did not disprove their 
contention that the victim had made a threatening move 
hariri was also ordered to pay damages of 556000 to air afrique 
and a total of 101000 to beaulieus family the flight attendent 
and a second passenger he threatened 
hariri commandeered an air afrique dc10 on a flight from 
brazzaville congo to paris on july 24 1987 to press demands for 
the release of lebanese and palestinians held by france west 
germany and israel 
after gaining control of the plane over northern italy he 
demanded to be flown to beirut but agreed to a refueling stop at 
geneva airport hariri shot beaulieu after his deadline for readying 
the plane expired 
swiss police stormed the plane and arrested the lone hijacker 
after crew members overpowered him and passengers began fleeing the 
aircraft over safety chutes 
flight attendant jeanpierre elouma was seriously injured by a 
shot from hariris pistol when he jumped the hijacker 
investigators said hariri boarded the plane at bangui central 
african republic carrying 140 rounds of ammunition and 19 ounces of 
explosives 
hariri refused to testify in court about his alleged links to the 
proiranian hezbollah group lebanons most militant faction 
presiding judge jeanjacques leu said hariri told pretrial 
interrogators that he joined hezbollah in 1985 after his release 
from an israeli prison 
hezbollah is believed to be an umbrella for groups holding most 
of the 15 foreign hostages in lebanon which include nine americans 
the longestheld foreign hostage is terry a anderson 41 chief 
middle east correspondent for the associated press who was 
kidnapped march 16 1985 
hariri had told interrogators he received detailed instructions 
for his mission 
swiss officials said his demands during negotiations at geneva 
airport included the release of the hamadi brothers two lebanese 
arrested in west germany as terror suspects 
one of them mohammed ali hamadi has been on trial in frankfurt 
since last july on charges linked to the 1985 hijack of a twa 
airliner to beirut in which a us navy diver was killed 
hariri told the court he did not intend to kill beaulieu but that 
he fired without aiming when the frenchman his head covered with a 
blanket made a threatening move 
i did not want to kill anyone i only wanted to liberate my 
friends said hariri who described himself as a soldier of 
god 
but the flight steward told the court he saw hariri kill beaulieu 
with a closerange shot to the head 
hariri acknowledged he paid a bribe equivalent to about 6 to 
elude police controls at the airport in bangui where his father 
reportedly had a business 
he was expected to be returned to the maximum security wing of 
genevas champdollon jail after sentencing 
the hariri case gained wider dimensions with the kidnap of a 
swiss red cross delegate in lebanon last november 
swiss foreign minister rene felber said the abduction was aimed 
gaining leniency for hariri the delegate of the allswiss 
international committee of the red cross peter winkler was 
released after a month in the hands of captors who were never 
identified switzerland said no concessions were made 
