<TEXT>
aflcio leaders concluded their annual 
winter meeting friday with a call on congress to make it tougher for 
employers to skim assets from pension funds and a vow to be a major 
force in the coming redrawing of congressional districts 
the federations executive council also condemned a recent 
treasury department reversal of a customs service determination that 
imported multipurpose vehicles were small trucks and therefore 
subject to a 25 percent import tariff 
the protracted labor dispute at eastern airlines dominated the 
weeklong meeting with leaders of the 141millionmember federation 
promising to back up 8500 machinists and ground personnel planning 
to strike the airline next week 
but labor also put on the record its positions on a variety of 
domestic and international issues with statements ranging from a 
call for an increased minimum wage to condemnation of irans 
ayatollah khomeini for his death threats against satanic verses 
author salman rushdie also included were resolutions supporting 
labor movements in poland hungary chile burma south africa 
malaysia and korea 
the friday resolution on pensions said nearly 2 million workers 
have had their pensions jeopardized since 1980 by employers who use 
overfunded pension money for business purposes primarily to help 
initiate or fight takeover attempts 
workers have a fundamental right to pension fund assets the 
35member executive council said employers who terminate pension 
plans to skim off excess assets violate that right and deprive 
workers and retirees of their pension protection 
the statement called on congress to take a number of steps to 
discourage employers from dipping into or terminating pension funds 
including provisions calling for distribution of excess assets 
between employers and plan beneficiaries 
the postelection year session of the council was not as 
political as past gatherings but the resolution on redistricting 
that will follow the 1990 census indicated labor would try to be a 
major force in maintaining democratic majorities in both the 
congress and the majority of state legislatures 
it is vital that the labor movement and its allies coordinate a 
longterm reapportionment strategy that assists state legislative 
candidates who are committed to programs that benefit working 
americans and counterbalances conservative antiunion efforts to 
gerrymander away liberal legislators the council said 
the resolution said the shape of redistricting would be affected 
by those elected to key posts in 1989 and 1990 elections and urged 
aflcio affiliates to use their political action money and resources 
to support project 500 and the national committee for an effective 
congress two liberaloriented organizations involved in the debate 
on how the redistricting should be carried out 
the resolution condemning treasurys decision in the 
multipurpose vehicle case was requested by owen bieber president 
of the united auto workers 
the initial customs ruling would have made usmade 
multipurpose vehicles predominantly smaller fourwheel drive 
vehicles more attractive in terms of price than those of foreign 
competitors mainly japanese auto makers 
