us authorities said friday that a 
swissbased currency trading company may have been involved in a 
massive moneylaundering scandal involving drugs in the united 
states 
the us embassy said in a statement that the possible role of 
the lebanesecontrolled shakarchi trading ag of zurich was 
revealed during the largest drug money laundering investigation 
ever conducted by us law enforcement agencies 
among many aspects revealed by this investigation in new york 
was the fact that a bank account maintained there by the shakarchi 
trading company in zurich may have been involved in transactions 
with some of the targets of the probe the statement said 
shakarchi trading ag is headed by a lebanese mohammed 
shakarchi its vice president until last oct 27 was hans w kopp 
the husband of former swiss justice minister elisabeth kopp 
mrs kopp resigned last month after admitting she tipped her 
husband off that the company might come under scrutiny by swiss 
authorities 
the companys name has been mentioned in connection with a probe 
launched by a swiss prosecutor into the origins of more than 2 
billion allegedly transferred to switzerland by two lebanese 
brothers jean and barkev magharian both are being held in lugano 
southern switzerland on suspicion of fraud 
mohammed shakarchi a business contact of the magharians has 
denied any part in drug money laundering swiss prosecutor dick 
marty said in a report this month that shakarchi told investigators 
he had warned a manager of credit suisse the counrtys third 
largest commercial bank that funds deposited by the magharians with 
the bank were of doubtful origin 
swiss government spokesman achille casanova told reporters friday 
swiss authorities were examining whether judicial proceedings can be 
opened against the shakarchi company he said the companys new york 
account contained 500000 believed by investigators to be drug 
money 
the us embassys news release said that during the us probe 
codenamed operation polar cap it emerged that the us 
government had in the past purchased foreign currency from the 
shakarchi trading company 
but it said these past legitimate purchases have no known 
bearing on any aspect of this or any other criminal investigation 
money laundering is not punishable in switzerland unless the 
funds are used for criminal purposes legislation to make it a 
criminal offense is being drafted 
