of dollarbuying after the federal reserve board announced it was 
raising its discount rate by a halfpoint to 7 percent 
the buying subsided after currency dealers decided the rate hike 
would have little impact 
an increase in the key rate which is the interest the fed 
charges on loans to private banking institutions was widely 
anticipated in light of the decision by the nations private banks 
to raise their prime lending rates 
on thursday and friday a series of major banks drove up the 
rates used as benchmarks for variable loan interest charges to 115 
percent from 11 percent 
